title: Prep roundup: SPASH dominates WVC meet
text:
Prep roundup: SPASH dominates WVC meet Daily Tribune Media 11:41 p.m. CDT October 1, 2015 Prep roundup CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
WAUSAU – The Stevens Point Area Senior High girls tennis team capped off adominant Wisconsin Valley Conference season Thursday in the conference meet at Wausau East. 
The Panthers claimed all four singles titles and sweet all three doubles to capture its third straight conference title with a whopping 126 points. 
Wausau East grabbed second with 65 points behind runner-up finishes for Sami Miles and Sydney Blaskowski at No. 1 and No. 2 singles, respectively, and Leah Blaskowski at No. 4 singles. 
Chloe Westberg and Quinn Lodholtz also placed second for the Lumberjacks at No. 2 doubles. 
Wausau West received strong runner-up performances from the No. 1 doubles team of Sarah Snoeyenbos, while Kaomi Yang and Sydney Turner were second at No. 3 doubles. 
In addition, Merrill’s Katie Nelson picked up a runner-up result at No. 3 singles. 
Championship matches 
Singles: No 1 - Emily Luetschwager (SPASH) def. Sami Miles (WE), 6-0, 6-0; No. 2 - Sabrina Tang (SPASH) def. Sydney Blaskowski (WE), 6-1, 6-0; No. 3 - Lily Firkus (SPASH) def. Katie Nelson (Me), 6-0, 6-1; No. 4 - Suzie DeBot (SPASH) def. Leah Blaskowski (WE), 6-0, 6-3. 
Doubles: No. 1 - Jaide Barber/Juliet Champion (SPASH) def. Sarah Snoeyenbos/Kate Peterson (WW), 6-4, 6-1; No. 2 - Kayla Stutesman/Madison DeBot (SPASH) def. Chloe Westberg/Quinn Lodholtz (WE), 6-0, 6-0; No. 3 - Emily Meier/Kaylee Bruneau (SPASH) def. Kaomi Yang/Sydney Turner (WW), 6-3, 6-1. 
CROSS COUNTRY 
Athens Invite 
ATHENS – Connor Dolan finished second overall and Seamus Dolan was fourth as the Assumption boys won the team title with 31 points. 
The Royals had six of the top 13 individuals overal as Sean Dolan and Anton Keuntjes were sixth and seventh, respectively. 
Athens’ Joshuah Langteau won the boys 5,000 meter race in 16 minutes, 45.2 seconds, finishing sis seconds ahead of Dolan. 
The Assumption girls placed fourth overall. Maria Gudelis was 13th overall to lead the Royals. 
VOLLEYBALL 
Wausau East 3, Wis. Rapids 0 
WAUSAU – Jordan Murphy had 22 assists and two aces and Lauren Luoma had 22 digs as the Lumberjacks swept the Wisconsin Valley Conference game 25-15, 25-10, 25-13. 
Becca Young had 12 kills and three aces for East. 
Merrill 3, D.C. Everest 2 
MERRILL – Anna Finnell had 24 kills and Emily Page had 51 assists as the Bluejays remained undefeated in the WVC. 
Ali Zamzow had a team-high 23 digs for the Bluejays who won 26-28, 25-16, 25-18, 21-25, 15-12. 
The Bluejays completed a season sweep of the Evergreens and improved to 7-0 in the conference. 
Regan Stefan had 16 kills and Natalie Mohring added 12 kills and 17 assists as the Evergreens fell to 5-2 in the WVC. 
Allyssa Frahm had a team-high 30 digs for Everest and Caroline Hehir had 24 assists. 
GIRLS SWIMMING 
SPASH 114, Wausau West 56 
WAUSAU – Julia Stupar won the 100 breaststroke in 1 minute, 12.69 seconds and the 200 freestyle in 2:02.27 to lead the Panthers to a WVC dual meet victory over the Warriors. 
Julia Bartram won the 100 butterfly (1:10.44) and was part of the Warriors’ winning 200 medley relay. 
SPASH improved to 4-0 in conference dual meets and West is 0-3.

Wausau East 123.5, Marshfield 46.5 
WAUSAU – Sydney Richetto and Hailey Bunkleman each won a pair of individual events and Richetto also was part of two winning relay teams in the Lumberjacks’ WVC dual meet win over the Tigers. 
Bunkleman won the 50-yard freestyle and 100 backstroke, while Richetto topped the field in the 200 and 100 freestyle events. 
Elizabeth Holbrook picked up second-place results in the 200 IM and 100 breaststroke to pace the Tigers.
